        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/364/449",
        "text": [
          "٣٦٤. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): لَا تَسْأَلْ عَمَّا لَا يَكُونُ، فَفِي الَّذِي قَدْ كَانَ لَكَ شُغُلٌ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "364. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: Do not ask about things which may not happen because you have enough to worry about with what happens."
